WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:51.084 --> 00:52.187
Huh?

00:53.319 --> 00:55.526
I am not a bum.

00:56.656 --> 00:58.191
I'm a jerk.

01:00.894 --> 01:04.397
I once had wealth, power,

01:05.498 --> 01:08.774
and the love
of a beautiful woman.

01:09.836 --> 01:13.511
Now, I only have two things.

01:14.808 --> 01:17.083
My friends

01:24.751 --> 01:26.560
and, uh, my thermos.

01:32.792 --> 01:33.895
Huh?

01:36.362 --> 01:37.897
My story?

01:47.307 --> 01:48.683
Okay.

01:51.978 --> 01:54.720
It was never easy for me.

01:56.116 --> 01:59.620
I was born
a poor black child.

02:01.554 --> 02:03.590
I remember the days

02:03.923 --> 02:06.596
sittin' on the porch
with my family

02:07.293 --> 02:11.164
singin' and dancin'
down in Mississippi.

02:11.164 --> 02:12.966
[Children screaming]

02:12.966 --> 02:14.536
[All chattering]

02:18.538 --> 02:20.984
Whoa Lordie
Pick a bale a day

03:11.658 --> 03:12.829
[neighing]

03:14.427 --> 03:15.528
[Meowing]

03:15.528 --> 03:17.730
Boy, I hope
everybody's good and hungry.

03:17.730 --> 03:19.465
I know I am.

03:19.465 --> 03:20.934
(Father)
And I'm ready for that.

03:20.934 --> 03:24.005
Here's corn bread
and collard greens.

03:24.270 --> 03:26.706
And I cooked up
those hog maws you like.

03:26.706 --> 03:29.311
Mother, dear, ain't we
forgetting somethin'?

03:30.143 --> 03:33.646
No, I'm not.
Today is Navin's birthday.

03:33.646 --> 03:35.682
[All exclaiming]

03:36.115 --> 03:37.383
Happy Birthday!

03:37.383 --> 03:38.985
Today is Navin's birthday.

03:38.985 --> 03:41.624
And I cooked you up
your favorite meal.

03:42.889 --> 03:45.725
Tuna fish salad on white bread
with mayonnaise

03:45.725 --> 03:48.394
a Tab,
and a couple of Twinkies.

03:48.394 --> 03:49.463
Here, darlin'.

03:49.729 --> 03:51.364
Gee, Mom, thanks.

03:51.364 --> 03:53.299
You're gonna
like that shit, man.

03:53.299 --> 03:55.608
[All laughing]

03:56.502 --> 03:57.981
I got you a present.

03:59.105 --> 04:00.607
Gee, Elvira.

04:00.607 --> 04:01.874
I made it myself.

04:01.874 --> 04:03.243
We got you somethin', too.

04:03.243 --> 04:04.978
A whole half bottle
of Lilac Vegetal.

04:04.978 --> 04:06.279
It's from both of us.
Gee.

04:06.279 --> 04:07.647
[Chuckling]

04:07.647 --> 04:09.249
I drew you this picture.

04:09.249 --> 04:10.583
Here.

04:10.583 --> 04:11.751
[Chuckling]

04:11.751 --> 04:13.019
(Navin)
Thank you.

04:13.019 --> 04:14.691
I want you to have my Zippo.

04:17.390 --> 04:18.560
Gee, Dad,

04:19.926 --> 04:21.995
you had this since the war.

04:25.265 --> 04:26.505
Thanks.

04:28.034 --> 04:29.706
[Choking]
Thanks, everybody.

04:31.237 --> 04:34.047
God bless us, every one.

04:35.141 --> 04:36.278
Navin.

04:37.543 --> 04:38.714
[Sniffling]

04:41.214 --> 04:45.018
Well,
will you pass me the potatoes
and the collard greens?

04:45.018 --> 04:46.519
Navin, darlin'?

04:46.519 --> 04:48.554
I'm sorry
I spoiled the party, Mom.

04:48.554 --> 04:50.556
Aw, you didn't
spoil the party.

04:55.495 --> 04:57.440
Navin, I brought you
a Twinkie.

05:00.066 --> 05:02.546
I'm not hungry right now.

05:03.870 --> 05:05.872
You feelin' different again,
huh?

05:06.272 --> 05:07.974
It's like I don't fit in.

05:07.974 --> 05:09.809
It's like
I don't belong here.

05:09.809 --> 05:11.010
[Sniffling]

05:11.010 --> 05:13.649
It's your birthday,
and it's time you knew.

05:14.314 --> 05:16.885
Navin, you're not
our natural-born child.

05:23.389 --> 05:24.629
I'm not?

05:26.326 --> 05:28.567
You were left on our doorstep.

05:29.062 --> 05:31.872
But we raised you
like you were one of us.

05:32.298 --> 05:34.471
You mean
I'm gonna stay this color?

05:35.468 --> 05:37.072
[Crying]

05:37.337 --> 05:39.972
Navin, I'd love you

05:39.972 --> 05:43.214
if you were the color
of a baboon's ass. Come here.

05:48.881 --> 05:50.121
Uh, Navin...

05:52.085 --> 05:54.721
Navin, I... I wrapped
your sandwich in cellophane,

05:54.721 --> 05:56.325
just like you like it.

05:57.757 --> 06:01.227
You, uh, wanna come in
and sing some blues?

06:02.061 --> 06:03.596
No thanks, Taj.

06:04.130 --> 06:06.473
There's somethin'
about those songs,

06:07.233 --> 06:08.835
they depress me.

06:08.835 --> 06:10.903
[Chuckling]
Come here, darlin'.

06:10.903 --> 06:12.473
[Laughing]

06:13.106 --> 06:14.414
[Scatting]

06:20.980 --> 06:22.754
That's it, darlin'.

06:24.717 --> 06:26.886
You're gettin' the rhythm,
see?

06:26.886 --> 06:28.797
[Continues scatting]

06:35.628 --> 06:38.798
(male announcer)
And that concludes
this Sunday Night Gospel Hour

06:38.798 --> 06:41.033
live from the Four Square
Gospel Church

06:41.033 --> 06:43.843
at the Divine Salvation
in St. Louis, Missouri.

06:44.070 --> 06:46.482
The Rev. Williard Willman,
Pastor.

06:46.706 --> 06:48.685
And now,
Music Throughout the Night.

06:48.808 --> 06:50.810
Music in a mellow mood.

06:50.810 --> 06:53.051
[Music playing on radio]

08:05.985 --> 08:08.988
Grandma!

08:08.988 --> 08:10.857
What happened?
What happened?

08:10.857 --> 08:12.892
Don't touch that radio!
Don't touch it!

08:12.892 --> 08:14.293
Turn it up! Turn it up!

08:14.293 --> 08:15.962
This is unbelievable!

08:15.962 --> 08:18.203
I've never heard
music like this before!

08:18.498 --> 08:21.734
It speaks to me!
Taj, Dad.

08:21.734 --> 08:24.170
This is unbelievable.
Now watch. Now watch.

08:24.170 --> 08:25.876
[Music continues playing
on radio]

08:28.040 --> 08:29.041
Yeah.

08:30.243 --> 08:31.944
Well, if this is out there,

08:31.944 --> 08:34.113
think how much more
is out there!

08:34.113 --> 08:36.148
This is the kind of music
that tells me

08:36.148 --> 08:38.287
to go out there
and be somebody!

08:39.418 --> 08:40.820
But, Navin.

08:40.820 --> 08:42.162
Let him go.

08:50.863 --> 08:54.500
Son, now that
you're goin' out
into the world,

08:54.500 --> 08:57.203
there's, uh, somethin'
you should know.

08:57.203 --> 08:58.404
[Whinnying]

08:58.404 --> 08:59.772
You see that?

08:59.772 --> 09:00.907
Yeah.

09:00.907 --> 09:02.341
That's shit.

09:02.341 --> 09:03.876
[Goat bleating]

09:03.876 --> 09:06.788
And this, Shinola.

09:09.615 --> 09:10.718
Shit.

09:12.285 --> 09:13.525
Shinola.

09:13.986 --> 09:16.193
Son, you're gonna be
all right.

09:16.689 --> 09:19.725
Now what town are you
gonna try for first?

09:19.725 --> 09:21.994
Well, I thought
I'd try to go to St. Louis

09:21.994 --> 09:24.630
'cause that's where that
radio show was coming from.

09:24.630 --> 09:28.200
And remember,
the Lord loves a workin' man.

09:28.200 --> 09:29.702
Lord loves a workin' man.

09:29.702 --> 09:32.739
And Son, don't never,
ever trust whitey.

09:33.072 --> 09:34.307
Don't trust whitey.

09:34.307 --> 09:37.043
The Lord loves a workin' man,
don't trust whitey.

09:37.043 --> 09:38.344
[Goat bleating]

09:38.344 --> 09:39.948
Oh, baby.

09:40.980 --> 09:42.390
Daddy.

09:45.351 --> 09:47.421
Pierre. Come here.

09:47.653 --> 09:49.922
Don't you forget
to grow up now.

09:49.922 --> 09:51.190
Good luck.

09:51.190 --> 09:53.225
Send me a picture postcard.

09:53.225 --> 09:54.627
Don't forget, baby.

09:54.627 --> 09:56.629
Okay, okay,
let the boy go.

09:56.629 --> 09:58.064
Bye.

09:58.064 --> 09:59.765
We got work to do.

09:59.765 --> 10:03.212
And I hope you find whatever
it is you're looking for.

10:03.736 --> 10:05.340
[Hens clucking]

10:06.105 --> 10:09.041
I will, Ma.
I know it's out there.

10:09.041 --> 10:11.210
It's out there all right,
and if you catch it,

10:11.210 --> 10:13.145
see a doctor
and get rid of it.

10:13.145 --> 10:14.513
See a doctor
and get rid of it.

10:14.513 --> 10:15.615
Good luck.

10:15.615 --> 10:16.983
The Lord loves a workin' man.

10:16.983 --> 10:18.351
Don't trust whitey.

10:18.351 --> 10:20.592
See a doctor
and get rid of it.

10:21.220 --> 10:22.699
Bye, Grandma.

10:24.924 --> 10:26.198
[Dog barking]

10:28.427 --> 10:29.701
[Sighing]

10:37.503 --> 10:39.642
Oh, I sure do miss Navin.

10:41.774 --> 10:44.083
(Elvira)
Is he ever comin' back?

10:44.744 --> 10:46.621
Take away
his place settin'.

10:46.746 --> 10:48.657
It's making us
too goddamn sad.

10:53.686 --> 10:56.029
I wonder
if he's doin' all right.

10:56.622 --> 10:59.102
Hey, Navin, how you doin'?

10:59.392 --> 11:00.693
Don't worry 'bout me.

11:00.693 --> 11:02.604
I think I see a car comin'.

11:02.895 --> 11:05.671
No wait, it's a truck.
It's a truck.

11:07.299 --> 11:10.939
Oh, Lord,
take care of our little boy.

11:11.337 --> 11:13.009
[Truck approaching]

11:16.976 --> 11:18.477
I'm hitchhikin'.

11:18.477 --> 11:19.712
How far you goin'?

11:19.712 --> 11:21.714
St. Louis.
How far are you goin'?

11:22.248 --> 11:24.250
To the end of this fence.

11:25.451 --> 11:26.554
Okay.

11:29.722 --> 11:30.890
[Door slams]

11:30.890 --> 11:33.793
I'm Navin Johnson.
What's your name, sir?

11:33.793 --> 11:35.203
Here we are.

11:35.528 --> 11:36.597
Okay.

11:42.468 --> 11:44.140
Thanks for the company.

11:45.071 --> 11:47.676
(Navin)
I hope
I can repay you someday.

11:51.277 --> 11:52.721
[Crickets chirping]

12:21.741 --> 12:23.618
[Snoring]

12:24.243 --> 12:26.154
[Dog barking]

12:39.692 --> 12:41.627
Well, what is it, boy?
Are you lost?

12:41.627 --> 12:42.762
[Barking]

12:42.762 --> 12:45.538
Do you want to play?
Is it trouble?

12:45.698 --> 12:47.142
[Yelping]

12:48.400 --> 12:51.745
Trouble? Is it an accident?

12:52.705 --> 12:55.412
A drownin'? A fire?

12:56.575 --> 12:57.843
Fire.

12:57.843 --> 12:59.322
[Exclaiming]

13:00.146 --> 13:03.249
Gosh, we've got
to warn everybody.

13:03.249 --> 13:05.251
I've heard
about dogs like you.

13:05.484 --> 13:07.153
You're gonna be famous.

13:07.153 --> 13:09.622
You're gonna... You're gonna
get your picture taken,

13:09.622 --> 13:11.390
and they'll put it
in the paper.

13:11.390 --> 13:14.700
Gosh, this is excitin'.
You saved my life.

13:15.294 --> 13:17.229
Come on,
let's warn everybody.

13:17.229 --> 13:19.470
Arf! Arf! Arf! Arf!

13:19.965 --> 13:21.233
Fire! It's a fire!

13:21.233 --> 13:22.501
[Woman screaming]

13:22.501 --> 13:25.271
There's a fire!
Everybody! Wake up.

13:25.271 --> 13:26.705
There's a fire!

13:26.705 --> 13:29.508
This dog,
he's saving everybody's life!

13:29.508 --> 13:30.943
He's unbelievable.

13:30.943 --> 13:32.945
He's some dog.
He's a lifesaver.

13:32.945 --> 13:35.381
(Navin)
That's what I'll call him,
too. Old Lifesaver.

13:35.381 --> 13:37.283
That's gonna be your name!

13:37.283 --> 13:39.763
[Siren wailing]

13:40.653 --> 13:43.722
Folks? False alarm.
There's no fire.

13:43.722 --> 13:45.599
[People chattering]

13:46.225 --> 13:49.128
Hey, mister, don't
call that dog "Lifesaver."

13:49.128 --> 13:50.296
No?

13:50.296 --> 13:51.900
Call him "Shithead."

13:52.565 --> 13:54.874
Good. Shithead.

13:56.068 --> 13:57.512
It's excitin'.

13:58.137 --> 14:01.914
It's just exciting to have
this kind of life on the road.

14:02.107 --> 14:03.676
A guy and his dog.

14:03.676 --> 14:05.416
[Truck honking]

14:08.347 --> 14:09.615
(man)
St. Louis?

14:09.615 --> 14:11.851
No. Navin Johnson.

14:11.851 --> 14:14.019
No, do you want a lift
to St. Louis?

14:14.019 --> 14:15.955
Oh! Okay, thanks.

14:15.955 --> 14:17.161
Hop in.

14:20.526 --> 14:23.063
(Navin)
This will be fine.
Right here.

14:30.836 --> 14:31.937
[Barking]

14:31.937 --> 14:33.347
Thank you.

14:35.074 --> 14:36.575
Where you goin'?

14:36.575 --> 14:38.054
To the bathroom.

14:38.377 --> 14:39.745
You gotta have a key.

14:39.745 --> 14:41.046
Can I get one?

14:41.046 --> 14:43.082
My key is for customers
who buy gas.

14:43.082 --> 14:44.083
Oh!

14:44.817 --> 14:46.261
I'm buying gas.

14:46.518 --> 14:47.962
I don't see no car.

14:48.888 --> 14:51.290
I... I just need enough
for my lighter.

14:51.290 --> 14:52.458
Oh, look at this.

14:52.458 --> 14:54.326
And my wife wanted me
to stay home today.

14:54.326 --> 14:55.794
Look what
I would have missed.

14:55.794 --> 14:58.063
A complete fill-up
for a whole lighter, huh?

14:58.063 --> 14:59.331
It's on that wall.

14:59.331 --> 15:00.366
Thank you.

15:01.934 --> 15:03.208
[Clanging]

15:08.974 --> 15:10.643
And don't walk away with it.

15:10.643 --> 15:11.917
I won't.

15:12.344 --> 15:13.646
[Knocking on door]

15:13.646 --> 15:15.214
(Harry)
Hey, pop-top.

15:15.214 --> 15:17.149
Hey, silverbird,
I'm talkin' to you.

15:17.149 --> 15:18.284
Huh?

15:18.284 --> 15:21.094
Listen, you wanna be president
of the Texaco Oil?

15:21.687 --> 15:22.922
Sure.

15:22.922 --> 15:25.026
Then clean up the sink
in there.

15:26.292 --> 15:28.897
Then I'll be
president of Texaco Oil?

15:29.662 --> 15:31.897
Whatever happened
to workin' your way up?

15:31.897 --> 15:33.799
He starts workin' for me
10 minutes

15:33.799 --> 15:35.869
and already
he wants to be president.

15:36.468 --> 15:38.170
Get to work in there.

15:38.170 --> 15:40.411
But, sir, I don't work here.

15:40.773 --> 15:42.877
Not even for $1. 10 an hour?

16:08.667 --> 16:11.971
(Navin)
"Dear Folks, I got this
great job in a gas station.

16:11.971 --> 16:14.239
"I don't wanna say
how much I'm getting,

16:14.239 --> 16:16.575
but let's just say
it's a lot."

16:16.575 --> 16:18.844
"I'm enclosing $2."

16:18.844 --> 16:20.948
That's a good boy.

16:21.413 --> 16:24.984
"It's a lot of fun working and
Mr. Hartounian is really nice.

16:24.984 --> 16:27.419
He's teaching me
how to be impatient."

16:27.419 --> 16:28.687
Navin!

16:28.687 --> 16:30.389
"Well, I gotta go now.

16:30.389 --> 16:33.233
What do you think I do,
write letters all day?"

16:35.661 --> 16:37.096
You actually
sleep here?

16:37.096 --> 16:38.506
Yes, is that okay?

16:39.698 --> 16:40.833
Come with me.

16:40.833 --> 16:43.335
I got a beautiful little place
for you to stay.

16:43.335 --> 16:46.247
Put the light on.
You're gonna like it here.

16:47.806 --> 16:49.008
Like it?

16:49.008 --> 16:52.478
I love it!
This is fabulous!

16:52.478 --> 16:55.288
I mean,
you got the toilet here.

16:55.614 --> 16:57.923
This must be
the kitchen. No.

16:59.485 --> 17:01.253
You know, what I could do

17:01.253 --> 17:04.189
is take this wall
and just turn it this way

17:04.189 --> 17:06.191
so I've got
a much larger living space,

17:06.191 --> 17:08.827
plus it'll create a flow
into the main living area.

17:08.827 --> 17:10.295
It'll be incredible.

17:10.295 --> 17:12.798
No, no, I'll just
elevate this about 6 inches.

17:12.798 --> 17:14.500
Create the illusion
of two rooms

17:14.500 --> 17:16.702
and yet still have that flow.

17:16.702 --> 17:19.605
Then I can take bookshelves
and put them here.

17:19.605 --> 17:22.107
No, I'll put the books
right over here.

17:22.107 --> 17:23.942
That way
I can be relaxed over here.

17:23.942 --> 17:26.011
The customers come in
and use the urinal.
Navin.

17:26.011 --> 17:28.079
I won't disturb them,
they won't disturb me.

17:28.079 --> 17:30.783
Take it easy, it's not here.
It's in here.

17:30.783 --> 17:31.784
Oh!

17:33.352 --> 17:35.422
I couldn't afford this,
anyway.

17:35.821 --> 17:37.459
Well, this is it.

17:38.957 --> 17:40.459
It's perfect.

17:40.459 --> 17:42.594
I won't have to
change this at all.

17:42.594 --> 17:43.970
Take a look.

17:44.129 --> 17:47.299
No kitchen, no windows,
no chairs, no tables.

17:47.299 --> 17:49.234
It's a masterpiece
of understatement.

17:49.234 --> 17:52.237
I'll put a bed down here,
get a bigger bulb.

17:52.237 --> 17:54.373
I'll bring some sheets
from the house.

17:54.373 --> 17:56.108
You'll be set for life.

17:56.108 --> 17:57.643
Gosh!

17:58.110 --> 18:00.089
How much is this
gonna cost me?

18:00.746 --> 18:01.880
Nothin'.

18:01.880 --> 18:04.690
When you're rich and famous,
you'll send me a postcard.

18:06.485 --> 18:08.089
A postcard, huh?

18:14.426 --> 18:16.462
Okay. It's a deal.

18:17.763 --> 18:19.139
It's a deal.

18:20.833 --> 18:22.468
What are those?

18:22.468 --> 18:24.770
(Harry)
Step outside
for a second, darlin'.

18:24.770 --> 18:26.605
Navin,
this is my wife, Lenore.

18:26.605 --> 18:28.240
Lenore, this is Navin.

18:28.240 --> 18:29.575
Pleased to meet you.

18:29.575 --> 18:31.677
Navin, do you know why
a woman of such pulchritude

18:31.677 --> 18:33.312
is married to a man
like me?

18:33.312 --> 18:35.347
'Cause I make
a very comfortable living.

18:35.347 --> 18:38.150
And this is the first time
I'm leaving you alone
on a Sunday.

18:38.150 --> 18:40.052
If anything should happen
to this station,

18:40.052 --> 18:42.293
this woman would leave me
like a...

18:44.089 --> 18:46.758
In other words,
there would be no more, uh...

18:46.758 --> 18:48.494
Do you know what
I'm talkin' about?

18:48.494 --> 18:50.098
Yes, sir. No more...

18:52.397 --> 18:55.467
So remember, guard
this station with your life.

18:55.467 --> 18:57.803
Because my sex life
is in your hands.

18:57.803 --> 18:59.475
[Car door closing]

19:00.472 --> 19:01.540
[Bell tinkling]

19:01.540 --> 19:03.019
[Tires screeching]

19:04.543 --> 19:05.851
[Engine revving]

19:09.948 --> 19:11.850
I can fix those shocks.

19:11.850 --> 19:15.320
No, no, we just want some gas,
muchacho.

19:15.320 --> 19:17.923
Okay, but it's Sunday.
We got to have a credit card.

19:17.923 --> 19:19.197
[Exclaiming]

19:19.358 --> 19:21.226
Then all the cash
is locked up?

19:21.226 --> 19:22.828
Oh, no, not locked up.

19:22.828 --> 19:24.196
We got a lot of cash.

19:24.196 --> 19:25.797
It's just that
the banks are closed,

19:25.797 --> 19:28.500
and I'm not allowed to have
cash coming in or going out

19:28.500 --> 19:30.335
'cause I'm here alone
for the first time.

19:30.335 --> 19:32.070
I don't want
anything to happen.

