59:25.495 --> 59:26.629
(Navin)
So, Mom,

59:26.629 --> 59:29.006
with my faithful dog
leading the way,

59:29.499 --> 59:31.740
I'm out to win
the hand of Marie.

59:32.335 --> 59:35.077
You'd love her, Ma.
She looks just like you.

59:35.572 --> 59:37.346
Except she's white and blond.

59:38.107 --> 59:41.711
So, to win her back,
I vowed to make
something of myself.

59:41.711 --> 59:44.614
I settled in Los Angeles
and took the money I saved

59:44.614 --> 59:46.749
and rented my
first apartment.

59:46.749 --> 59:48.451
"I haven't heard from Marie.

59:48.451 --> 59:49.719
[Hen clucking]

59:49.719 --> 59:51.020
"Things couldn't be worse.

59:51.020 --> 59:53.556
I can only send you
49 cents this week..."

59:53.556 --> 59:55.124
Oh, bless his heart.

59:55.124 --> 59:56.659
That's a good boy.

59:56.659 --> 59:58.763
"...as I've lost all my jobs.

59:59.729 --> 01:00:01.230
"I've been
eating well, though.

01:00:01.230 --> 01:00:04.334
"The hospital gives out
free meals of orange juice
and cookies.

01:00:04.334 --> 01:00:06.814
"And all I have to do
is give them a pint of blood.

01:00:07.537 --> 01:00:10.707
I ate there all week.
Three times a day."

01:00:10.707 --> 01:00:11.874
A pint of blood?

01:00:11.874 --> 01:00:13.476
"I decided to quit

01:00:13.476 --> 01:00:16.946
"when I cut myself shaving
and nothing came out but air.

01:00:18.181 --> 01:00:22.424
"I have to go now
as someone is staring at me
through binoculars.

01:00:22.852 --> 01:00:24.661
Your loving son, Navin."

01:00:28.057 --> 01:00:29.627
It's him.

01:00:36.866 --> 01:00:37.935
Him?

01:00:42.839 --> 01:00:44.477
What's him doing here?

01:00:45.041 --> 01:00:46.679
Shithead! Shithead!

01:00:47.844 --> 01:00:50.113
Attack! Attack! Attack!

01:00:50.113 --> 01:00:51.247
[Growling]

01:00:51.247 --> 01:00:52.521
Not me!

01:00:54.484 --> 01:00:55.894
Get off, Shithead!

01:00:58.788 --> 01:01:00.023
[Screaming]

01:01:00.023 --> 01:01:01.797
(madman)
You son of a bitch.

01:01:01.958 --> 01:01:03.300
[Screaming]

01:01:45.935 --> 01:01:47.277
[Panting]

01:01:55.078 --> 01:01:56.989
You're gonna have
to sign for this.

01:01:59.949 --> 01:02:01.985
I have to sign
before you shoot me?

01:02:02.518 --> 01:02:04.258
I'm not gonna shoot you.

01:02:05.621 --> 01:02:06.756
Why not?

01:02:06.756 --> 01:02:08.132
That was the old me.

01:02:08.424 --> 01:02:10.631
I was a little mixed-up
at that time.

01:02:10.993 --> 01:02:14.235
Had a bad marriage
and I just gave up smoking.

01:02:14.897 --> 01:02:16.501
I'm okay now.

01:02:17.700 --> 01:02:19.645
I'm a private detective.

01:02:26.909 --> 01:02:28.077
So long.

01:02:28.077 --> 01:02:29.453
(Navin)
Thank you.

01:02:37.453 --> 01:02:39.296
"Dear Mr. Johnson.

01:02:40.590 --> 01:02:42.865
"Please call on me in Suite

01:02:44.160 --> 01:02:48.039
"2655 at
the Century Plaza Tower

01:02:48.331 --> 01:02:49.502
"in Los Angeles.

01:02:50.867 --> 01:02:53.472
"I have something
of great importance

01:02:54.604 --> 01:02:56.083
to impart to you."

01:02:56.572 --> 01:02:58.949
Navin! Remember me?

01:03:00.309 --> 01:03:02.078
No, but don't feel bad.

01:03:02.078 --> 01:03:03.318
Fox.

01:03:04.413 --> 01:03:05.687
(Stan)
Stan Fox!

01:03:06.249 --> 01:03:08.353
Remember the gas station?

01:03:09.652 --> 01:03:12.962
Boy, you are one hard guy
to find!

01:03:15.892 --> 01:03:17.530
You don't remember me.

01:03:19.228 --> 01:03:21.435
The glasses handle! Look!

01:03:23.833 --> 01:03:24.936
Oh, yeah.

01:03:25.501 --> 01:03:26.869
My glasses handle.

01:03:26.869 --> 01:03:28.439
Use the Opti-Grab.

01:03:28.805 --> 01:03:30.072
Opti-Grab?

01:03:30.072 --> 01:03:31.674
Yeah, we call it Opti-Grab.

01:03:31.674 --> 01:03:32.975
Opti-Grab.

01:03:32.975 --> 01:03:34.385
"Opti," from the eye

01:03:34.744 --> 01:03:37.156
and "Grab,"
from where you grab it.

01:03:37.680 --> 01:03:39.352
Opti-Grabbing it.

01:03:39.715 --> 01:03:41.854
(Stan)
Navin, my boy,
we're in business.

01:03:42.018 --> 01:03:44.225
Fifty-fifty.
Just like we said.

01:03:44.887 --> 01:03:47.731
Right in here,
I have your first check

01:03:48.457 --> 01:03:51.028
for 250 big ones.

01:03:51.961 --> 01:03:53.201
$250?

01:03:53.996 --> 01:03:56.874
That's just the beginning.
There's gonna be more.
Lots more!

01:03:57.400 --> 01:03:59.068
Can I cash this?
Sure.

01:03:59.068 --> 01:04:02.138
You can do whatever you like.
It's your money.
It's a cashier's check.

01:04:02.138 --> 01:04:03.139
Wow!

01:04:03.673 --> 01:04:05.083
I can use money.

01:04:05.608 --> 01:04:09.312
(Navin)
Yes, I have a cashier's check

01:04:09.312 --> 01:04:10.847
and I'd like to cash it.

01:04:10.847 --> 01:04:12.121
How much is it for?

01:04:12.682 --> 01:04:16.595
250 big ones.

01:04:21.424 --> 01:04:24.700
250 dollarinies.

01:04:27.129 --> 01:04:31.202
(Navin)
That's 250 doughnuts.

01:04:31.834 --> 01:04:33.502
[Typewriters clacking]

01:04:33.502 --> 01:04:35.003
You wanna cash this?

01:04:35.371 --> 01:04:38.241
Well, I could take
50 of the doughnuts

01:04:38.241 --> 01:04:41.077
and deposit
the other 200 beauties.

01:04:41.077 --> 01:04:42.812
Have a seat, Mr., uh,

01:04:42.812 --> 01:04:43.847
Johnson.

01:04:46.148 --> 01:04:48.517
I will need two pieces
of identification.

01:04:48.517 --> 01:04:51.054
Ah, yes. I have my

01:04:51.387 --> 01:04:53.696
temporary driver's license.

01:04:54.824 --> 01:04:58.703
And my Astronaut
Application form.

01:05:00.062 --> 01:05:03.566
I didn't pass that, though.
I failed everything
but the "Date of Birth."

01:05:04.000 --> 01:05:05.376
I didn't get the job.

01:05:06.002 --> 01:05:07.370
Everything's in order.

01:05:07.370 --> 01:05:10.506
If you'll, uh, just
endorse this, right there.

01:05:10.506 --> 01:05:11.807
I need a pen.

01:05:11.807 --> 01:05:12.909
Pen. Okay.

01:05:12.909 --> 01:05:14.710
Right here. Thank you.

01:05:14.710 --> 01:05:18.214
And, uh, fill out this, uh,
deposit slip right there.

01:05:18.214 --> 01:05:19.488
All right.

01:05:20.116 --> 01:05:23.927
The endorsing and filling out
of the deposit slip.

01:05:24.553 --> 01:05:28.262
Two hundred and fifty...

01:05:28.958 --> 01:05:30.562
thousand...

01:05:42.605 --> 01:05:45.210
"Dear Harry. Guess what?

01:05:45.741 --> 01:05:48.077
"I'm rich beyond
my wildest dreams.

01:05:48.077 --> 01:05:50.012
"But I haven't
forgotten our deal.

01:05:50.012 --> 01:05:51.948
"Here's that postcard
I promised you.

01:05:51.948 --> 01:05:54.428
"I'll bet you thought
you'd never get it, huh?

01:05:54.850 --> 01:05:56.795
Your friend forever, Navin."

01:05:57.219 --> 01:05:58.857
How do you like that?

01:05:59.155 --> 01:06:02.158
He promised me a postcard
and he sent me a postcard.

01:06:02.792 --> 01:06:04.566
The kid has integrity.

01:06:22.912 --> 01:06:24.618
(Navin)
Shithead, come on.

01:06:27.616 --> 01:06:28.924
[Phone ringing]

01:06:39.195 --> 01:06:41.538
Yello. Yes.

01:06:42.565 --> 01:06:43.600
Who?

01:06:44.400 --> 01:06:45.844
Mrs. Kimball?

01:06:47.303 --> 01:06:49.009
You're Marie's mom!

01:06:49.872 --> 01:06:51.646
Read about me in the paper?

01:06:52.308 --> 01:06:54.844
I've been trying
to contact her.
I don't know where she is.

01:06:54.844 --> 01:06:56.482
I'd give anything to find out.

01:06:58.047 --> 01:06:59.617
That sounds a little high.

01:07:00.282 --> 01:07:01.886
How about $75?

01:07:03.119 --> 01:07:04.222
Okay.

01:07:04.520 --> 01:07:05.726
Okay. What is it?

01:07:06.288 --> 01:07:08.958
The May Company
in Los Angeles.

01:07:08.958 --> 01:07:10.960
(Navin)
Shithead!
I know where she is!

01:07:10.960 --> 01:07:12.200
I know where she is!

01:07:12.328 --> 01:07:14.296
(Marie)
Doesn't that feel good?

01:07:14.296 --> 01:07:16.036
Mmm-hmm.

01:07:17.833 --> 01:07:20.245
(Marie)
There. Now, we are complete.

01:07:22.605 --> 01:07:25.041
Putting on Mask-O Derm
just took a few short minutes

01:07:25.041 --> 01:07:27.843
and when we peel it off,
he will look 20 years younger.

01:07:27.843 --> 01:07:29.151
Allevei.

01:07:29.278 --> 01:07:30.586
Yes, exactly.

01:07:31.213 --> 01:07:32.648
Now we'll let this dry.

01:07:32.648 --> 01:07:34.717
In the meantime,
we can go pick out

01:07:34.717 --> 01:07:36.719
an eye shadow
and lip tint for him.

01:07:36.719 --> 01:07:38.788
Now everyone just
follow me this way

01:07:38.788 --> 01:07:41.090
because this is
a very interesting line.

01:07:41.090 --> 01:07:42.558
I think you'll enjoy this.

01:07:42.558 --> 01:07:44.493
With your husband's coloring,

01:07:44.493 --> 01:07:47.329
a deep tone would
bring out his lips.

01:07:47.329 --> 01:07:51.572
And this Nature Beige
will feature his eyes
just wonderfully.

01:07:51.801 --> 01:07:53.871
(Tillie)
Let's try everything.

01:07:56.539 --> 01:07:57.574
What?

01:07:58.707 --> 01:07:59.809
Ah!

01:07:59.809 --> 01:08:01.677
Let's go unmask Irving.

01:08:01.677 --> 01:08:03.451
Everyone, back this way.

01:08:04.346 --> 01:08:07.516
We are now going
to peel off our Mask-O Derm.

01:08:07.516 --> 01:08:09.689
Irving's skin will
be tighter, firmer,

01:08:09.819 --> 01:08:12.054
and he'll look like
a different man.

01:08:12.054 --> 01:08:13.430
You'll be amazed.

01:08:14.457 --> 01:08:16.027
Get ready, Irving.

01:08:28.938 --> 01:08:30.473
[Crowd gasping]

01:08:30.872 --> 01:08:33.716
Jeez! This shit
really worked.

01:08:37.279 --> 01:08:38.314
Navin.

01:08:41.050 --> 01:08:42.585
Oh, my sweetheart.

01:08:42.585 --> 01:08:43.685
[All gasping]

01:08:43.685 --> 01:08:47.022
What are you doing
to my husband,
you Miss Blondie? Irving!

01:08:47.022 --> 01:08:48.890
Irving, are you crazy?

01:08:48.890 --> 01:08:50.359
(Navin)
"Dear Mom.

01:08:50.359 --> 01:08:52.294
"The big news is,
Marie and I were married.

01:08:52.294 --> 01:08:53.500
"We couldn't wait.

01:08:53.796 --> 01:08:56.999
"Luckily, we found someone at
the Hollywood View Apartments,

01:08:56.999 --> 01:08:59.001
"who could marry us
immediately.

01:08:59.435 --> 01:09:01.537
"He was a certified priest.

01:09:01.537 --> 01:09:03.380
[Exclaims]

01:09:04.173 --> 01:09:06.845
"We were both glad
we had a religious wedding.

01:09:07.343 --> 01:09:09.515
"Money hasn't changed
our lives that much.

01:09:10.112 --> 01:09:11.779
"Our one little
extravagance is

01:09:11.779 --> 01:09:13.883
a live-in butler
and housekeeper."

01:09:13.883 --> 01:09:15.117
Another check!

01:09:15.117 --> 01:09:16.218
[Chuckles]

01:09:16.218 --> 01:09:18.663
Just as I thought.
Look at that.

01:09:18.888 --> 01:09:21.162
Nearly $750,000.

01:09:21.457 --> 01:09:24.660
Sir, it would seem
with this kind of income,
you could buy a larger house

01:09:24.660 --> 01:09:26.332
with proper
servants' quarters.

01:09:26.662 --> 01:09:29.031
(Navin)
"Mom, remember my dream
of owning

01:09:29.031 --> 01:09:30.698
"a big house on a hill?

01:09:30.698 --> 01:09:32.939
"How I used to
wish for a living room

01:09:33.068 --> 01:09:35.343
"with a plaster lion
in it from Mexico?

01:09:35.770 --> 01:09:39.241
"And how I always wanted
a large 24-seat dining table?

01:09:39.375 --> 01:09:42.243
"In a dining room
with original oil paintings

01:09:42.243 --> 01:09:44.814
"by Michelangelo
and Rembrandt?

01:09:45.281 --> 01:09:48.216
"And remember how
I always wanted a rotating bed

01:09:48.216 --> 01:09:50.752
"with pink chiffon
and zebra stripes?

01:09:50.752 --> 01:09:53.354
"And remember how
I used to chitchat with Dad

01:09:53.354 --> 01:09:57.030
"about always wanting
a bathtub shaped like a clam?

01:09:57.259 --> 01:09:59.966
"And an office with orange
and white stripes?

01:10:00.196 --> 01:10:01.764
"And remember
how much I wanted

01:10:01.764 --> 01:10:04.676
"an all-red billiard room
with a giant stuffed camel?

01:10:05.501 --> 01:10:08.811
"And how I wanted
a disco room
with my own disco dancers?

01:10:09.205 --> 01:10:11.344
"And a party room
with fancy friends?

01:10:12.775 --> 01:10:14.410
"And remember
how much I wanted

01:10:14.410 --> 01:10:16.612
"a big back yard
with Grecian statues

01:10:16.612 --> 01:10:19.149
"S-shaped hedges
and three swimming pools?

01:10:19.415 --> 01:10:21.087
"Well, I got that, too.

01:10:24.053 --> 01:10:25.930
"Marie and I
are getting along swell.

01:10:26.822 --> 01:10:30.269
"But I've got a lot to learn
about handling
my money and banks.

01:10:30.826 --> 01:10:32.236
"You have to be careful.

01:10:34.363 --> 01:10:35.569
"Poor Hobart.

01:10:36.265 --> 01:10:37.933
"His dear wife Hester
took some money

01:10:37.933 --> 01:10:41.303
"out of her savings account
and had to pay
a substantial penalty

01:10:41.303 --> 01:10:42.838
"for early withdrawal.

01:10:47.610 --> 01:10:50.215
Enclosed is
this week's check.
Love, Navin."

01:10:51.614 --> 01:10:53.388
Sorry about
your wife, Hobart.

01:10:53.849 --> 01:10:55.692
Federal regulations, sir.

01:10:56.719 --> 01:10:57.890
Oh, dear me.

01:10:58.287 --> 01:11:00.562
Your wife has given you

01:11:00.990 --> 01:11:02.434
another gold chain.

01:11:03.392 --> 01:11:04.734
I'd nearly forgotten.

01:11:05.561 --> 01:11:09.164
[Sighing]
I suppose, I'm still not quite
over Hester's death.

01:11:09.164 --> 01:11:10.833
Well, these things take time.

01:11:10.833 --> 01:11:11.967
Yes.

01:11:11.967 --> 01:11:14.913
So I'm told.
Oh, here's your drink, sir.

01:11:15.104 --> 01:11:17.208
Like the one you
saw in the magazine.

01:11:17.473 --> 01:11:20.317
You got the bamboo umbrella
and everything.

01:11:23.479 --> 01:11:26.289
See that? Be somebody.

01:11:28.684 --> 01:11:31.790
Very good, sir.
Very good.

01:11:33.389 --> 01:11:34.757
Oh, uh,

01:11:34.757 --> 01:11:37.396
there are some charity people
here to see you, sir.

01:11:37.660 --> 01:11:40.003
No! Send them away!

01:11:40.396 --> 01:11:43.032
There's a lot of people
more deserving than me.

01:11:43.032 --> 01:11:45.637
Ah, but these people
want you to give.

01:11:47.770 --> 01:11:48.771
Oh.

01:11:50.673 --> 01:11:51.708
Okay.

01:11:51.974 --> 01:11:54.977
My name is
Father Carlos Las
Vegas De Cordoba.

01:11:56.145 --> 01:11:58.284
Father, you seem
like a religious man.

01:11:59.114 --> 01:12:00.422
How can I help you?

01:12:00.649 --> 01:12:02.890
By giving me three minutes
of your time

01:12:03.085 --> 01:12:04.820
so that you can see some film

01:12:04.820 --> 01:12:07.596
of a great ugliness
that is spreading
in my country.

01:12:08.590 --> 01:12:11.400
Oh, God.
I'll bet it's disgusting.

01:12:12.628 --> 01:12:13.762
Hobart?

01:12:13.762 --> 01:12:14.863
Yes, sir?

01:12:14.863 --> 01:12:17.099
Are you over your grief
enough yet to dim the lights?

01:12:17.099 --> 01:12:18.701
[Chuckling]
Of course, sir.

01:12:18.701 --> 01:12:20.737
Well, one can't mourn forever.

01:12:21.370 --> 01:12:24.077
You will not believe
what you are about to see.

01:12:24.907 --> 01:12:27.512
That human beings
could have sunk so low

01:12:27.676 --> 01:12:29.778
that they can take
pleasure to do this

01:12:29.778 --> 01:12:31.714
to another
of God's creatures.

01:12:31.714 --> 01:12:33.853
I hope you have
a strong stomach, senor.

01:12:34.483 --> 01:12:35.893
Roll the ugliness.

01:12:36.885 --> 01:12:38.364
[Men yelling]

01:12:46.462 --> 01:12:47.804
[All cheering]

01:12:58.040 --> 01:13:00.383
[Kittens purring]

01:13:15.290 --> 01:13:16.525
Good Lord.

01:13:16.525 --> 01:13:18.971
I've heard about
this cat juggling.

01:13:20.763 --> 01:13:22.071
[Men hooting]

01:13:37.713 --> 01:13:41.092
Stop it! Stop it! Stop it!
Stop it!

01:13:43.018 --> 01:13:44.053
Good.

01:13:45.154 --> 01:13:49.295
Father, could there be a God
that would let this happen?

01:13:50.726 --> 01:13:52.296
How much do you want?

01:13:52.828 --> 01:13:56.173
(man)
If your initial investment
is $500,000,

01:13:56.598 --> 01:13:58.771
and your apartments
are up in March,

01:13:59.501 --> 01:14:01.570
you should have
"X" amount of dollars

01:14:01.570 --> 01:14:03.806
rolling in
by the end of this year.

01:14:03.806 --> 01:14:06.875
(Navin)
Ah! "X" amount.
That's very good, isn't it?

01:14:06.875 --> 01:14:08.811
(Man #2)
Not only that,
you can depreciate

01:14:08.811 --> 01:14:10.746
the entire building
for the full amount.

01:14:10.746 --> 01:14:13.351
(Navin)
Depreciate? Very good.
Hmm. I like that.

01:14:14.216 --> 01:14:16.685
We found a way
to get around
this Fair Housing crap.

01:14:16.685 --> 01:14:19.529
Ah! Good.
Getting around the crap.
That's good.

01:14:20.289 --> 01:14:23.959
By keeping the rents high,
we're going to appeal to
a select class of people.

01:14:23.959 --> 01:14:25.961
Select class.
Very, very good.

01:14:27.196 --> 01:14:29.064
We'll keep the eggplants out.

01:14:29.064 --> 01:14:31.767
Ah, good.
We don't want any vegetables.

01:14:31.767 --> 01:14:34.136
No, no.
The jungle bunnies.

01:14:34.136 --> 01:14:36.240
Of course.
They'll eat the vegetables.

01:14:37.139 --> 01:14:39.312
Boss?
Can I... can I talk to him?

01:14:40.008 --> 01:14:42.078
We're gonna keep out
the niggers.

01:14:42.911 --> 01:14:44.079
The what?

01:14:44.079 --> 01:14:46.281
The niggers.
We'll keep 'em out.

01:14:46.281 --> 01:14:47.382
Yeah.

01:14:47.382 --> 01:14:51.330
Sir, you are talking
to a nigger!

01:14:54.423 --> 01:14:56.300
[Screaming]

01:14:56.859 --> 01:15:03.573
[Grunting]

01:15:13.942 --> 01:15:15.716
[Groaning]

01:15:30.526 --> 01:15:32.335
[Screaming]

01:15:34.897 --> 01:15:36.740
[Groaning]

01:15:38.667 --> 01:15:40.976
(Marie)
Don't be so hard on yourself.

01:15:41.103 --> 01:15:43.879
How could you know
that was Iron Balls McGinty?

01:15:44.673 --> 01:15:46.575
Your escargots. Salad.

01:15:46.575 --> 01:15:48.213
[People chattering]

01:15:48.343 --> 01:15:51.380
Would monsieur care
for another bottle
of the Chateau Latour?

01:15:51.380 --> 01:15:54.850
Ah, yes, but no more 1966.
Let's splurge.

01:15:55.017 --> 01:15:56.852
Bring us some fresh wine.

01:15:56.852 --> 01:15:58.186
The freshest you've got.

01:15:58.186 --> 01:16:00.791
This year's.
No more of this old stuff.

01:16:01.957 --> 01:16:03.265
Oui, monsieur.

01:16:03.926 --> 01:16:06.963
He doesn't realize
he's dealing with
sophisticated people here.

01:16:08.130 --> 01:16:10.232
Marie, now just stay calm.
Stay calm.

01:16:10.232 --> 01:16:11.533
(Navin)
Just don't look down.

01:16:11.533 --> 01:16:13.268
Don't look down!
Look up!

01:16:13.268 --> 01:16:16.112
Just keep your eyes up
and keep them that way, okay?
Waiter!

01:16:19.107 --> 01:16:21.743
There are snails
on her plate.

01:16:21.743 --> 01:16:23.313
[Squealing]

01:16:24.179 --> 01:16:26.715
Now get them out of here
before she sees them.

01:16:26.715 --> 01:16:29.525
Look away! Just look away!
And keep your eyes that way!

01:16:30.018 --> 01:16:32.854
You'd think at
a fancy restaurant like this,
at these prices,

01:16:32.854 --> 01:16:35.698
you would be able
to keep the snails
off the food!

01:16:36.558 --> 01:16:39.027
There're so many snails
in there, you can't even
see the food!

01:16:39.027 --> 01:16:40.429
Now take them away
and bring me

01:16:40.429 --> 01:16:43.332
those melted cheese
sandwich appetizers
you talked me out of!

01:16:43.332 --> 01:16:44.776
Oui, monsieur.

01:16:45.867 --> 01:16:47.436
Do you believe this?

01:16:47.436 --> 01:16:49.838
First, they didn't have
the bamboo umbrellas
for the wine

01:16:49.838 --> 01:16:51.473
and now snails
on the food.

01:16:51.473 --> 01:16:54.351
(Navin)
Two boobs!
That's what he takes us for!

01:16:55.877 --> 01:16:57.117
[Honking]

01:17:06.054 --> 01:17:07.123
Hi, honey.

01:17:07.255 --> 01:17:08.423
Hi, doll face.

01:17:08.423 --> 01:17:09.858
Everything okay?

01:17:09.858 --> 01:17:13.669
Remember how you told me
to take unnecessary lessons?

01:17:14.062 --> 01:17:16.198
Well, I just took
a lesson.

01:17:16.198 --> 01:17:17.799
And a very
good student, too.

01:17:17.799 --> 01:17:19.701
Adios, senora.
Adios.

01:17:19.701 --> 01:17:21.339
You took bullfighting?

01:17:21.570 --> 01:17:23.413
No. Knife-throwing.

01:17:25.007 --> 01:17:26.486
(Navin)
Knife-throwing is great!

01:17:26.608 --> 01:17:28.087
I can almost do it.

01:17:28.543 --> 01:17:30.012
Well, let me
see your stuff.

01:17:30.012 --> 01:17:31.547
Okay.

01:17:32.714 --> 01:17:34.716
This is very good
for a beginner.

01:17:37.386 --> 01:17:39.729
This is exciting.
I love this!

01:17:40.455 --> 01:17:41.592
Come on.

01:17:43.258 --> 01:17:45.594
(Marie)
Turn sideways.
Okay.

01:17:45.594 --> 01:17:48.074
And put a balloon
in your mouth.

01:17:48.497 --> 01:17:50.169
Do you have a balloon?

01:17:50.298 --> 01:17:51.777
Uh, no.

01:17:52.267 --> 01:17:53.711
Oh, wait. Yes.

01:17:54.903 --> 01:17:56.109
(Marie)
Okay.

01:17:57.239 --> 01:17:58.674
Is it in your mouth?

01:17:58.674 --> 01:17:59.775
Uh-huh!

01:17:59.775 --> 01:18:02.346
Throw 'em good
and hard so they'll stick.

01:18:03.045 --> 01:18:04.319
Okay.

01:18:07.582 --> 01:18:08.651
One,

01:18:09.551 --> 01:18:10.654
two,

01:18:12.120 --> 01:18:13.189
three!

01:18:14.222 --> 01:18:15.325
Four, five, six!

01:18:18.660 --> 01:18:19.661
Oh!

01:18:20.395 --> 01:18:21.669
I missed.

01:18:22.164 --> 01:18:23.665
Honey, you did good.

01:18:24.433 --> 01:18:26.674
I can't do anything right.

01:18:27.569 --> 01:18:30.276
Honey, you worry too much.

01:18:31.573 --> 01:18:35.179
Come on. Let's flop this over
and look at it another way.

01:18:35.410 --> 01:18:38.513
Why, do you realize
in the past two short months,

01:18:38.513 --> 01:18:41.049
we have acquired
the sophistication

01:18:41.049 --> 01:18:43.927
it takes some people
a lifetime to acquire?

01:18:44.152 --> 01:18:45.528
Come on!

01:18:46.121 --> 01:18:47.361
Let's toast!

01:18:49.991 --> 01:18:51.435
[People chattering]

01:18:59.234 --> 01:19:00.713
[Crowd cheering]

01:19:45.313 --> 01:19:49.056
(woman)
Everybody, Navin's on TV.
Marie, it's Navin!

01:19:49.317 --> 01:19:52.454
Oh, honey, here's that
interview you did on TV.

01:19:52.454 --> 01:19:55.423
Shut off the music!
Shut it off!
Shut off the music!

01:19:55.423 --> 01:19:58.293
Everyone,
we're going to watch Navin
on the TV.

01:19:58.293 --> 01:20:01.239
Now, sit down.
Just sit on the floor.
Sit around.

01:20:01.730 --> 01:20:03.799
(Clete Roberts)
American Time Newsmagazine,

01:20:03.799 --> 01:20:05.903
turns its probing eye
on Navin Johnson,

01:20:06.034 --> 01:20:07.808
inventor of the Opti-Grab.

01:20:08.103 --> 01:20:10.238
That little glasses handle
that sold

01:20:10.238 --> 01:20:12.877
10 million units in
a few short months.

01:20:13.475 --> 01:20:16.785
(Clete Roberts)
Mr. Johnson, you've become
a millionaire overnight.

01:20:17.045 --> 01:20:18.319
Who are you?

01:20:19.548 --> 01:20:21.254
Who is Navin Johnson?

01:20:22.617 --> 01:20:24.886
Navin is
a complex personality,

01:20:24.886 --> 01:20:27.389
as are most of
the small breed

01:20:27.389 --> 01:20:29.835
of modern-day
Renaissance millionaires.

01:20:30.125 --> 01:20:33.795
(Clete Roberts)
We had planned to show you
the entire Johnson interview.

01:20:33.795 --> 01:20:35.764
However, when we
returned to our studio,

01:20:35.764 --> 01:20:37.666
our news department
informed us

01:20:37.666 --> 01:20:40.840
of a sensational development
in the Johnson story.

01:20:41.269 --> 01:20:43.772
It seems that
an irate group of citizens

01:20:43.772 --> 01:20:46.808
led by the celebrity
Mr. Carl Reiner,

01:20:46.808 --> 01:20:49.945
has filed a class-action suit
against Mr. Johnson

01:20:49.945 --> 01:20:51.413
and his Opti-Grab.

01:20:51.413 --> 01:20:54.482
Here's what Mr. Reiner had
to say at a press conference.

01:20:54.482 --> 01:20:57.719
When Opti-Grab came out,
I thought it was
the greatest thing ever.

01:20:57.719 --> 01:20:58.959
And I bought a pair.

01:20:59.421 --> 01:21:01.093
And this is the result.

01:21:01.289 --> 01:21:02.460
[All gasping]

01:21:03.058 --> 01:21:04.960
(Carl)
This little handle is
like a magnet.

01:21:04.960 --> 01:21:09.067
Your eyes are
constantly drawn to it
and you end up cockeyed.

01:21:09.764 --> 01:21:12.904
Now, as a director,
I am constantly using my eyes.

01:21:13.101 --> 01:21:15.103
And this Opti-Grab
device has caused

01:21:15.103 --> 01:21:17.014
irreparable harm to my career.

01:21:17.505 --> 01:21:19.814
Let me show you
a clip from my latest film,

01:21:19.941 --> 01:21:22.216
where my faulty
depth perception kept me

01:21:22.344 --> 01:21:24.619
from yelling "cut"
at the proper time.

01:21:27.749 --> 01:21:28.920
(Carl)
Cut!

01:21:38.126 --> 01:21:40.162
(Carl)
If I had yelled "cut" on time,

01:21:40.295 --> 01:21:42.741
those actors
would be alive today.

01:21:43.164 --> 01:21:47.442
That's why I'm spearheading
the $10-million
class-action suit

01:21:47.702 --> 01:21:51.377
against Mr. Johnson
and his irresponsible
selling of a product,

01:21:51.606 --> 01:21:54.177
he didn't even test
on prisoners.

01:21:54.943 --> 01:21:56.011
Thank you.

01:21:56.011 --> 01:21:58.380
(woman)
The party's over.
Nouveau riche.

01:21:58.380 --> 01:22:00.282
You know what I mean?

01:22:00.282 --> 01:22:02.918
What is this?
Hey, wait a second.
Where are you going?

01:22:02.918 --> 01:22:04.552
(man)
This guy's something else.

01:22:04.552 --> 01:22:06.759
I'm gonna get in touch
with that Reiner guy.

01:22:07.188 --> 01:22:10.091
I got some... I got some
change upstairs.

01:22:10.091 --> 01:22:13.197
We'll get some, uh,
potato chips and
there's some beer up there.

01:22:13.395 --> 01:22:15.670
We'll make it
a less formal thing.

01:22:16.031 --> 01:22:17.198
[Crowd chattering]

01:22:17.198 --> 01:22:19.041
(man)
